reviews.text:
After a poor experience with a competitive company we took a chance calling JR Pressure Wash and Sealer relative to our need to have our circle driveway cleaned, re-sanded, and sealed.  They arrived according to schedule, were well prepared, executed every phase with professional expertise, were extremely courteous, and didn't miss a detail. The results: our driveway looks BRAND NEW!
We are very pleased with JR Pressure Wash and Sealer and we would not hesitate to recommend them to anyone who is looking for dependable, honest, performance.
Bud and Ann Elias

This company was awesome and affordable. The owner is who came out to do the estimate and initial inspection. He was professional and caring to my concerns/needs not only personally but for my home. They were fast, efficient, and left no mess! When it came time to the service the servicemen were professional and kind and you could tell they used a teamwork approach. This company made the process easy with great communication and was honest in expectations. I only searched one time on Google pressure washing companies near me and used the first one that popped up. I‚Äôm glad it was you guys as I didn‚Äôt look further based on the reviews and what I saw already online from this company. You have earned me as a customer for future needs and will recommend to others. I am so excited for my new front porch and back patio furniture to be delivered now. Thank you!

Excellent service! This company is extremely professional.  Our roof was in serious need of a cleaning. The owner came out for the estimate and I was immediately impressed by his professionalism. The office was efficient and responsive. The cleaning guys did an amazing job and we're very thorough, even making sure to protect my landscape and plants! I'm looking forward to them doing our driveway over to repair the damage that somebody did well doing a lousy job sealing it!

We recently engaged the services of JR Pressure Wash and from the very outset we realized this was a first rate company. From the moment we spoke with Vicky on the phone to when Jared the owner came by, we realized they would be high on our list. They have a great website that explains their whole process. Jared came to us and spent at least 45 minutes further explaining how he would approach our particular job. He did use Google maps to get a feel for the size of the paver and brick surfaces we wanted washed, sanded and sealed, but also took more exact measurements on site for a more accurate proposal.
They worked with us on scheduling and rescheduling due to rain. Kevin and Justin arrived right on time and spent the next 8 hours pressure washing our driveway, walkways, 2 patio areas and brick pool deck. They then "sanded" all our pavers and finally put down the sealer. It all looks brand new. Kevin and Justin couldn't have been nicer or more professional. They took my constant "supervision" in stride. I only saw them take a short break for lunch. Really knowledgeable, hard workers.
I highly recommend this company. BJolley. Safety harbor, FL

I hired JR Pressure Washing to clean an older home in preparation for sale. They did a great job. House looked like new when they were done. What I loved most about JR Pressure Washing is their timely communications. They never kept me waiting  and always provided me with the information I needed.

We had had some less than stellar experiences with some of these companies in the past, and were looking for firms with a focus on customer satisfaction and attention to detail. We saw Hydro Force listed with positive reviews on Google, Angie‚Äôs List, and Home Advisor so we decided to ask them to bid on our project. After filling out the contact information requesting a free estimate on their web site, we received a call back from Tom, the owner, within thirty minutes and this was on Super Bowl Sunday! After describing our project to Tom, he told us he would be by on Monday afternoon to look at the job and give us an estimate. True to his word, Tom called on Monday afternoon to say he was on the way, and arrived within thirty minutes. He walked the entire property and took measurements for everything we wanted done. He showed us his insurance information as well as before and after pictures of other jobs Hydro Force had done, and explained what would be done at our location. By Monday evening we had Tom‚Äôs bid for our job.
Our Board of Directors voted to accept the Hydro Force bid based on their presentation and professionalism. While it was not the lowest bid, it was very competitive and that factored into our decision. We agreed on a start date and time for the project and on the appointed date Tom and his wife Connie, arrived ten minutes early and proceeded to go to work. They worked from nine in the morning until four in the afternoon, stopping only briefly for lunch. Their attention to detail is absolutely first rate, and customer focus is obviously a priority.
Let us finish by saying that if you are contemplating a project involving pressure washing, whatever it might be, you really should at least get a bid from Tom at Hydro Force. Professional, Punctual, and Priced right. We will definitely be using them again in the future.

address: 6236 93rd Terrace N APT 3506, Pinellas Park, FL 33782, United States

reviews.text: Reached out to American Pressure Washing based on their google reviews and they called right away. The price they gave was the best quote we received. Kyle and his wife Chelsea showed up on time, super polite and professional. They quickly got to work and did a phenomenal job. Highly recommend these guys! Thank you again

Having just read Kyle's reviews, I'm happy to hear others have not had our experience in working with him and his wife. We accepted Kyle's proposal to clean, repair, re-sand and reseal our pavers on the pool deck on Feb 6, 2024. They walked off the job yesterday, May 24, 2024,  leaving quite a mess for us to clean up. This was not the first time they did this.

When they first started, they pressure washed the pool deck, re-sanded and put a coat of sealer on over the old sealer which bled through the new sealer in splotches of white areas. Kyle appeared to be confused, but admitted that they should have stripped the old sealer before applying the new sealer. In a series of fits and starts, they attempted to strip the old sealer. In the process they washed approximately 50 lbs of sand into the swimming pool. We paid Pinch a Penny $150 to vacuum it out.

At the same time, there were several areas where pavers needed to be leveled and reset. Although Kyle agreed to do this, he never did and when I asked him about it he said some were too difficult and he didn't remember agreeing to fix the others. It didn't get done. They also washed sand into the tracks of our sliding glass doors and hurricane shades, and sprayed sand onto patio furniture, our grill, and onto plants in the planters and left us to take care of it. When we asked them to take care of it, they seemed insulted and from that point on Kyle has behaved like a petulant child.

Later, after weeks of not showing up because they had pushed other jobs ahead of ours, they pressure washed the pavers again and applied a stripper. Both sand and stripper were dumped into the pool. The pool water turned a bright green that has been very difficult to correct. We're still at it. They also killed a large plant and other plants have been compromised but look like they will survive.

In all cases, when I mentioned these issues to Kyle or offered some alternative approaches, he did not accept any responsibility, only offered excuses, or in most cases, no response all at.

Again, after over of month of the project being incomplete, they came on the 23rd and 24th to re-sand again and reseal. I had to insist that they protect the channels for the hurricane shades from sand intrusion, which earlier had caused them to not raise and lower correctly. I also asked them to be careful about getting sand and chemicals into the pool, but they either ignored my request of were unable to accomplish it. We have had to treat the pool with a product called First Aide and clean the filter almost daily.

When they walked off the job yesterday, again a big mess for us to take care of. You can see that in the photos. Water bottles, paper towels, steel wool and 5 gallon buckets were left scattered around our yard and into planters. They left all of the plastic and tape used to protect the hurricane shades and pool deck drains.

Kyle gives a good first impression, but be careful, make sure you put everything in writing and inspect everything before they leave the work site each day. Best, however, to go with another company.

The overall process from quote to finished job was simple and quick. Chelsea remained in constant communication during the process and through unforeseeable weather delays. The finished product turned out great. I would highly recommend American Pressure LLC to anyone looking to have their pavers cleaned and sealed.

Kyle is a great guy and an even better pressure washer. I‚Äôve been using him for years and every year I feel my house looks better and better outside. Not only is his quality high, but his pricing is accommodating and affordable.

You want your house to look good? Use this guy.

Estimate was in line and done in a professional manner with no sales pitch.
Job took longer than expected and with additional work & materials with no added fee.  ( We took care of it though) as it was handled very well when we were told.  Solid business practice.
Kyle and his wife Chelsea work as a well organized team during the entire process of stripping, cleaning, scrubbing, sanding and sealing.  Drains, pool handles and drain cover taped prior to application of the sealer.
Best job I‚Äôve seen done yet on pool pavers.
I‚Äôd highly recommend American Pressure for your power washing, pool decks, patios and other washing needs.
